commit.message:
TeX reader: support unicode-math Greek symbols, e.g. `\Alpha`.

This includes symbols like `\Alpha` and `\omicron` that weren't
defined in original TeX.

Closes #235.
Update typst tests: use partial instead of diff (typst 0.11).

TeX reader: convert Bin symbols to Ord when appropriate.

E.g. in '-3', we should have an Ord rather than a Bin, so
the spacing will be appropriate.

Closes #234.

Pandoc writer: fix spacing inside EDelimited.

Previously spaces around binary operators were omitted when
they occurred inside parens or brackets.  See #234.

Typst writer: avoid explicit `lr` when not necessary.

Closes #233.

Typst writer: add `\` to characters needing escape.

See #232.

Typst writer: use ASCII symbols when possible instead of symbols.

E.g., `+` instead of `plus`.
See #232.
Typst writer: add to list of characters that need escaping.

Typst writer: fixed EBoxed output.

Use display math mode inside `[]` and add a border.

Handle `\ddot` better in conversion to typst.

Closes #231.

TeX reader: handle `*{5}{lr}` in array column specifier.

Closes #229.

OMML reader: allow m:e to be missing in m:nary.

Technically this is not allowed, according to the spec, but
programs seem to tolerate it.

Closes #228.
Update tests for OOML writer change.

OMML writer: use "on" and "off" instead of "1" and "0"...

for m:CT_OnOff type.  It is said that "1" and "0" work in Word
but not Powerpoint.
